== Channel: approvals (ACTIVE - published AND consumed) ==

ApprovalAPI -> Hooks : emitApprovalNew(id, action, risk)
Hooks -> WSServer : broadcast("approvals", "new", data)
WSServer --> ApprovalUI : Socket.IO event: "new"
note right of ApprovalUI
  useRealtimeEvent(["approvals"], "new", handler)
  Falls back to polling if WS unavailable
end note

ApprovalAPI -> Hooks : emitApprovalDecided(id, status)
Hooks -> WSServer : broadcast("approvals", "decided", data)
WSServer --> ApprovalUI : Socket.IO event: "decided"

== Channel: dashboard (ACTIVE - published AND consumed) ==

FlowExec -> Hooks : emitDashboardRefresh("flow-execution")
Hooks -> WSServer : broadcast("dashboard", "refresh", { reason })
WSServer --> DashboardUI : Socket.IO event: "refresh"
DashboardUI -> DashboardUI : Refetch KPI data

note right of DashboardUI
  useRealtimeEvent(["dashboard"], "refresh", handler)
  Falls back to setInterval(30s) polling
  when WS unavailable (Vercel)
end note

== Channel: flow-execution (DEAD - published but NOT consumed via WS) ==

FlowExec -> Hooks : emitFlowStarted(flowId, execId)
Hooks -> WSServer : broadcast("flow-execution", "started", data)
WSServer --> FlowUI : **NEVER RECEIVED**
note right of FlowUI
  No client subscribes to
  "flow-execution" channel via WS.
  SSE is used instead.
end note

FlowExec -> Hooks : emitNodeComplete(flowId, nodeId, status, duration)
Hooks -> WSServer : broadcast("flow-execution", "nodeComplete", data)
WSServer --> FlowUI : **NEVER RECEIVED**

FlowExec -> Hooks : emitFlowFinished(flowId, execId, status)
Hooks -> WSServer : broadcast("flow-execution", "finished", data)
WSServer --> FlowUI : **NEVER RECEIVED**

== Channel: agent-status (DEAD - defined but NEVER published) ==

note over WSServer, FlowUI
  "agent-status" channel is defined in
  events.ts WsChannel type.
  emitAgentStatusChanged() exists in hooks.ts
  but NO API route calls it.
  NO client subscribes to it.
end note

== Channel: cost-update (DEAD - defined but NEVER published) ==

note over WSServer
  "cost-update" channel is defined in
  events.ts WsChannel type.
  emitCostRecorded() exists in hooks.ts
  but NO API route calls it.
  NO client subscribes to it.
end note

== Actual Flow Execution Real-Time: SSE Path ==

SSEClient -> SSE : GET /api/flows/[id]/execute-sse\n(Accept: text/event-stream)
SSE --> SSEClient : SSE: event "start" { nodeCount }
loop Per node
  SSE --> SSEClient : SSE: event "node_start" { nodeId, type }
  SSE --> SSEClient : SSE: event "node_done" { nodeId, status, duration }
end
SSE --> SSEClient : SSE: event "done" { success, executionId }

note right of SSEClient
  SSE replaces WS for flow execution.
  No Socket.IO needed.
  Works on Vercel (serverless).
  Client parses events from ReadableStream.
end note

== Polling Fallback (Vercel / WS unavailable) ==

WSServer ..> Polling : WS disconnected
Polling -> Polling : setInterval(30s)\nfetch("/api/dashboard")
Polling --> DashboardUI : Refreshed data

legend right
  **Summary: 5 channels defined**
  * approvals: ACTIVE (2 publishers, 1 subscriber)
  * dashboard: ACTIVE (1 publisher, 1 subscriber)
  * flow-execution: DEAD CODE (published, not consumed)
  * agent-status: DEAD CODE (never published, never consumed)
  * cost-update: DEAD CODE (never published, never consumed)

  **Transport options**
  1. Socket.IO WS (dev / self-hosted)
  2. SSE stream (flow execution only)
  3. Polling fallback (30s, Vercel)
